  script:
  - speaker: 0
    dialog: ...Uhh... hello?
  - speaker: 1
    dialog: ...
  - speaker: 0
    dialog: ...
  - speaker: 0
    dialog: Hey.
  - speaker: 0
    dialog: You, with the horns.
  - speaker: 1
    dialog: '!?!'
  - speaker: 1
    dialog: You can see me!?!
  - speaker: 0
    dialog: ...Yes?
  - speaker: 0
    dialog: What are you doing? Why are you just... standing there?
  - speaker: 1
    dialog: '!'
  - speaker: 1
    dialog: Nevermind that!
  - speaker: 1
    dialog: '*ahem*'
  - speaker: 1
    dialog: <color=red>TREMBLE MORTALS AND DESPAIR, DOOM HAS COME TO THIS WORLD!
  - speaker: 0
    dialog: ...
  - speaker: 0
    dialog: Cool.
  - speaker: 0
    dialog: Anyway, could you just not today? I already have enough to deal with.
  - speaker: 1
    dialog: Aww, what's the matter buddy? Wanna tell me about it?
  - speaker: 0
    dialog: 'I bullshitted my way into this intership with the Apothecary and I have
      no idea what I''m doing. '
  - speaker: 1
    dialog: Dude, that's not cool.
  - speaker: 0
    dialog: I had a good reason! I really needed the money.
  - speaker: 0
    dialog: How else would I be able to feed my candle addiction?
  - speaker: 1
    dialog: 'Well questionable ethics aside, today''s your lucky day! '
  - speaker: 1
    dialog: I happen to be in the business of helping people like you.
  - speaker: 1
    dialog: For a small fee of course...
  - speaker: 1
    dialog: Just blindly sign this contract on the red dotted line, and I'll help
      you with your internship!
  - speaker: 0
    dialog: ...
  - speaker: 0
    dialog: What could possibly go wrong? You've got a deal!
  - speaker: 0
    dialog: '*signs the contract*'
  - speaker: 1
    dialog: Fantastic! You've got yourself one genu-ine, bonafide, electrified Deal
      With The Devil.
  - speaker: 0
    dialog: Deal with the wh-
  - speaker: 1
    dialog: Now, let's get started. You see that <color=yellow>blue bar in the top
      right of the screen</color>? The one with the Apothecary's face?
  - speaker: 1
    dialog: That bar represents what the Apothecary thinks of you. Folks 'round here
      call it a <color=yellow>Reputation Bar</color>. Keep him happy, it'll fill
      up.
  - speaker: 1
    dialog: Fail his tasks, however, and you'll lose reputation. <color=yellow>Lose
      enough reputation, and you're fired</color>! No candles for you!
  - speaker: 0
    dialog: What a nightmare...
  - speaker: 1
    dialog: So yeah, keep him happy. Oh, wanna see something cool?
  - speaker: 1
    dialog: <color=red>*poof*
  - speaker: 1
    dialog: I've got a bar too!
  - speaker: 1
    dialog: Piss me off, and I'll drag you back to Hell with me.
  - speaker: 1
    dialog: But you seem chill. I'm sure that won't happen.
  - speaker: 1
    dialog: Probably.
  - speaker: 0
    dialog: Wonderful.
  - speaker: 1
    dialog: I know, right!?! Now, <color=yellow>return to the Apothecary</color>
      and tell him you've settled in. He'll give you your first task.
  - speaker: 1
    dialog: I'll help you out once you come back here. Oh and don't forget, <color=yellow>you
      can run by holding the shift key</color>.
  - speaker: 0
    dialog: Ugh.
